<Class name="CM_EDITrackedItem" id="d045979d-ab39-4bc0-a098-cff1bf625b67">
    <superclass name="CM_Object"/>
    <subclassPersistentAllowed/>
    <subclassSharedTransientAllowed/>
    <subclassTransientAllowed/>
    <abstract/>
    <text>!!PLEASE NOTE THE FOLLOWING WHEN ADDING NEW ATTRIBUTES OR SUBCLASSES!!:

MAKE THE ENTRY TABLE ROW NAME THE SAME AS THE ATTRIBUTE NAME
This is necessary for the generic user-defined EDI load functionality.

To write out any that don't match, run
UiCommonSchema&gt;&gt;JadeScript::th2EDIAttributesRecon


An CM_EDITrackedItem class must be created for each syle of data supported by EDI.
Each class must have a corresponding CM_EDIData class. One-to-one.
The association is created in CM_EDIForm::getTIType.

Adding collections to an EDI TrackedItem
as a sample see CM_EDIVoyageTI::allValidOperatorsCode
make sure there is a method that can change the string to a collection.
this should be called in setForUpdate(called when user updates) and assignValueSpecial (called for User defined updateas)
and setPropertyFromField (update for Internal XML).
Note: User Defined uses the name in the EtDef for the EDITI.
Internal XML uses the propertyName.

</text>
