    <PrimAttribute name="cargoType" id="5f59677b-66d1-42cf-97d1-4104b985b2c7">
        <embedded/>
        <type name="Integer"/>
        <access>readonly</access>
        <text>This will be set to the appropriate cargo type id once the supplied cargo type descr field has been validated.
</text>
    </PrimAttribute>
    <PrimAttribute name="cargoTypeDescr" id="f34942fa-4aeb-48d7-8b5f-2e77b968f7e8">
        <length>31</length>
        <embedded/>
        <type name="String"/>
        <text>This field contains either the original data from the user for the cargo type or the appropriate Cargo Type Description.

The supplied data can be either:
1) The cargo type abbreviation eg CONT in which case it will be replaced with the appropriate Cargo Type Description eg ISO Container.
2) Or the Cargo Type Description (case insensitive).
3) If invalid then it will be lefted as supplied.

If the supplied data is valid then the appropriate cargo type id will be moved to cargoType.

</text>
    </PrimAttribute>
